Lithobates berlandieri is a species of frog from the family Ranidae. 
They have a smooth and moist skin that varies in color from green to brown with dark blotches. 
Their eyes are large and positioned on top of their head. 
Lithobates berlandieri have strong and muscular legs that allow them to jump long distances. 
They can grow up to 12 cm in length. 
They are commonly found in freshwater habitats such as streams, rivers, and ponds in southern United States, Mexico, and Central America. 
Their diet consists mainly of insects, spiders, and other small invertebrates.
